creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Astounding Stories, May 1931 by Various.
Read in English by Bill Boerst
This issue of the science-fiction magazine includes a novella by Charles W. Diffin titled "Dark Moon" and several short stories, including "When Caverns Yawned," "When the Moon Turned Green," and "The Death-Cloud." There is also a second part of "The Exile of Time" by Ray Cummings. - Summary by Bill Boerst
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
